      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A LITTLE SILENCE NZ (4) is a progressive gelding who has managed two wins and two seconds from four WA starts since switching from NZ. Drew on the back row and raced three wide without cover last time but fought well to be beaten by 1.4 metres. Gets his best draw since winning from this barrier last month. Can return to the winners' list. SWEET PINS NZ (6) turned in a much better effort last time out, coming from the back row and finishing second at this circuit and distance. Should be hitting his peak now. Leading hope. HIGH PRICE (8) draws wide but did very well for fourth when resuming at Group 3 level behind topliner Magnificent Storm. That is good form for this so he looms as a serious challenger. BAZAAR PACKAGE (7) must be respected off a string of top-two finishes.",
